data.title: Robbie Williams XXV TOUR
data.meta_description: Robbie Williamsas jubiliejinį solinės karjeros šou surengs Lietuvoje.
data.text:
British singer Robbie Williams will perform the anniversary show of his solo career in Lithuania. It has been officially confirmed that Robbie Williams, who is returning to our country after a six-year break, will perform at the country’s biggest concert venue, Zalgirio Arena in Kaunas, Lithuania, on 10 March. The popular singer will present his recently released anniversary album “XXV” and perform all his most popular hits.

Tickets for Robbie Williams’ concert will be available at all Bilietai.lt box offices and online at www.bilietai.lt from 11am this Friday (30 September). On Wednesday (28 September) from 11am the first tickets will be available to members of the Robbie Williams Fan Club and the Live Nation Lithuania Concert Club (registration for the Live Nation Lithuania Concert Club: http://bit.ly/LiveNationConcertClub).

Robbie Williams – “Let Me Entertain You”:

The British superstar will be visiting Lithuania for the third time and the temporary capital for the second time. The first Robbie Williams show in Kaunas in the spring of 2015 was a huge success: all tickets were sold out in record time. Six years ago, the singer staged a grandiose performance in Vilnius Vingis Park, which became the biggest show of 2017 in the Baltics.

Robbie Williams – “Rock DJ” (Live at Knebworth):

Robbie Williams celebrates 25 years of his solo career. One of the world’s most popular performers is scheduled to visit 18 countries for 22 concerts. “The XXV Tour will kick off on 20 January in Bologna, Italy, and will be followed by concerts in many European cities, including Kaunas.

Robbie Williams – “Feel” (Live at Knebworth):

Robbie Williams’ solo career is celebrated with the release of the album XXV. His greatest hits were recorded with the renowned Metropole Orkest. Based in the Netherlands, this jazz and popular music orchestra is the largest of its kind in the world, with up to 97 musicians.

“I put many of my favourite songs on XXV. Each one has a special place in my heart, so to record them again with an orchestra was a really exciting process,” says the renowned British singer.

Robbie Williams – “Angels” (XXV) (with Metropole Orkest):

The album, featuring the new singles “Angels”, “Eternity”, “The Road To Mandalay” and the new song “Lost”, debuted at the top of the UK best-seller list. This is Robbie Williams’ 14th No 1 album, beaten only by Sir Paul McCartney. Counting his recordings with Take That, this is Robbie Williams’ 19th best-selling album in the UK.

Robbie Williams – “Lost” (XXV) (with Metropole Orkest):

Robbie Williams, who made his solo debut more than two decades ago in the boy band Take That, started his solo career in 1996 and has won 18 BRIT Awards – more than any other artist or band. He has also won three MTV Europe awards and has been the most played singer on British radio and TV for the past decade.

Robbie Williams – “Millenium”:

Robbie Williams is only the third singer to receive the prestigious BRITs Icon award, the third artist to be honoured with the prestigious award. Sir Elton John and David Bowie have been awarded BRITs Icon awards.

Robbie Williams – “Supreme”:

No fewer than 6 Robbie Williams albums are among the top 100 best-selling albums in UK history. Worldwide, more than 75 million albums and singles have been sold. Robbie Williams’ discography includes dozens of hits that have become popular around the world, including ‘Feel’, ‘Angels’, ‘Millennium’, ‘Let Me Entertain You’, ‘Kids’, ‘Supreme’, ‘Rock DJ’, and many others.
